[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":121},["Reactive",2],{"content-query-5tn5FDFj54":3},{"_path":4,"_dir":5,"_draft":6,"_partial":6,"_locale":7,"title":8,"description":9,"body":10,"_type":116,"_id":117,"_source":118,"_file":119,"_extension":120},"/docs/core-tech/using-beamx-roulette-contract-with-cli-wallet","core-tech",false,"","Using BeamX Roulette Contract With CLI Wallet","Let's play some games!",{"type":11,"children":12,"toc":113},"root",[13,20,25,48,53,58,63,73,78,87,92,100,105],{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":16,"children":17},"element","p",{},[18],{"type":19,"value":9},"text",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":21,"children":22},{},[23],{"type":19,"value":24},"In this example we will interact with the contract that",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":26,"children":27},{},[28,30,39,41],{"type":19,"value":29},"As usual we assume that you have read ",{"type":14,"tag":31,"props":32,"children":36},"a",{"href":33,"rel":34},"https://github.com/BeamMW/beam/wiki/BeamX-Getting-Started",[35],"nofollow",[37],{"type":19,"value":38},"BeamX Getting Started Guide",{"type":19,"value":40}," and ",{"type":14,"tag":31,"props":42,"children":45},{"href":43,"rel":44},"https://github.com/BeamMW/beam/wiki/Using-BeamX-Faucet-contract-with-CLI-Wallet",[35],[46],{"type":19,"value":47},"Using BeamX Faucet contract with CLI Wallet",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":49,"children":50},{},[51],{"type":19,"value":52},"We also assume that you have the app.wasm and contract.was in the shaders/roulette folder under the 'beamx' folder where you keep your wallet binary file.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":54,"children":55},{},[56],{"type":19,"value":57},"If so, we are all set to spin our Roulette.",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":59,"children":60},{},[61],{"type":19,"value":62},"Well, it's a kind of roulette. In our case your bet is on any number between 0 and 36 (including both 0 and 36). If you guess the number exactly you receive 100 tokens (which are actually new confidential assets on Beam chain). This actually means that in order to create a new Roulette contract you would need to lock the new asset type deposit (which in this chain is configured to be 1000 Beam)",{"type":14,"tag":64,"props":65,"children":66},"ol",{},[67],{"type":14,"tag":68,"props":69,"children":70},"li",{},[71],{"type":19,"value":72},"How do I play?",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":74,"children":75},{},[76],{"type":19,"value":77},"Since Roulette contract has an implicit owner (who is the dealer) there could be many roulettes out there. To find all of them we will run the following command:",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":79,"children":80},{},[81],{"type":14,"tag":82,"props":83,"children":84},"code",{"className":7},[85],{"type":19,"value":86},"beam-wallet-beamx.exe shader --shader_app_file shaders\\roulette\\app.wasm --shader_args=\"role=player,action=bet,cid=ac16be1cb673ace9423d32fe20893e1639fd560e35e6b3433c77bee831647372,iSector=15\" -n 127.0.0.1:8501",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":88,"children":89},{},[90],{"type":19,"value":91},"To check the status of your bet run",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":93,"children":94},{},[95],{"type":14,"tag":82,"props":96,"children":97},{"className":7},[98],{"type":19,"value":99},"beam-wallet-beamx.exe shader --shader_app_file shaders\\roulette\\app.wasm --shader_args=\"role=player,action=check,cid=ac16be1cb673ace9423d32fe20893e1639fd560e35e6b3433c77bee831647372\" -n 127.0.0.1:8501",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":101,"children":102},{},[103],{"type":19,"value":104},"To get your winning run:",{"type":14,"tag":15,"props":106,"children":107},{},[108],{"type":14,"tag":82,"props":109,"children":110},{"className":7},[111],{"type":19,"value":112},"beam-wallet-beamx.exe shader --shader_app_file shaders\\roulette\\app.wasm --shader_args=\"role=player,action=take,cid=ac16be1cb673ace9423d32fe20893e1639fd560e35e6b3433c77bee831647372\" -n 127.0.0.1:8501",{"title":7,"searchDepth":114,"depth":114,"links":115},2,[],"markdown","content:docs:core-tech:Using-BeamX-Roulette-contract-with-CLI-Wallet.md","content","docs/core-t